            "description": "Maasai Mara (Masai Mara) is situated in south-west Kenya and is one of Africa’s Greatest Wildlife Reserves. It is named in honor of the Maasai people, the ancestral inhabitants of the area, and the Mara River that runs through it. The reserve is renowned for its exceptional population of lions, leopards, cheetahs, elephants, and the annual migration of wildebeest and zebras. The Maasai Mara offers a quintessential African safari experience with its vast savannahs, diverse wildlife, and stunning landscapes.",
